---
// Static mock of a posted review: a diff hunk with one AI finding and one
// scanner finding, styled to echo GitHub's PR review UI. No screenshot needed.
---

<div class="ccr-mockup" role="img" aria-label="Example pull request review with an inline AI comment and a dependency CVE finding">
  <div class="ccr-mockup__bar">
    <span class="ccr-mockup__dot ccr-mockup__dot--r"></span>
    <span class="ccr-mockup__dot ccr-mockup__dot--y"></span>
    <span class="ccr-mockup__dot ccr-mockup__dot--g"></span>
    <span class="ccr-mockup__file">src/handlers/upload.ts</span>
  </div>

  <div class="ccr-mockup__code"><span class="del">- const dest = path.join(UPLOAD_DIR, req.body.filename)</span>
<span class="add">+ const dest = path.join(UPLOAD_DIR, sanitize(req.body.filename))</span>
   await fs.writeFile(dest, buf)</div>

  <div class="ccr-mockup__comment">
    <div class="ccr-mockup__avatar" aria-hidden="true">V</div>
    <div>
      <span class="ccr-tag ccr-tag--important">IMPORTANT · security</span>
      <p><strong>Path traversal</strong> — <code>req.body.filename</code> flows into <code>path.join</code> unsanitized, so <code>../../etc/passwd</code> escapes the upload dir.</p>
      <p>Why it matters: an attacker controls the write path and can overwrite arbitrary files.</p>
      <div class="ccr-suggestion">
        <div class="ccr-suggestion__hd">Suggested change</div>
        <div class="ccr-suggestion__body">const dest = path.join(UPLOAD_DIR, sanitize(req.body.filename))</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ccr-mockup__comment">
    <div class="ccr-mockup__avatar" aria-hidden="true">V</div>
    <div>
      <span class="ccr-tag ccr-tag--critical">CRITICAL · security</span>
      <p><code>lodash@4.17.20</code> is affected by prototype pollution.</p>
      <p class="ccr-prov">via OSV · GHSA-jf85-cpcp-j695 — fixed in 4.17.21</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
